Iconic Nigerian singer, Chibuzor Oji, popularly known as Faze has lost his mother. The Nigerian singer, lost his mother on the 12th of January at the age of 76, this comes barely a year after the death of his twin sister. Meet twin stars making waves in Hausa entertainment sector New initiative aspires to change Africa’s global media coverage methods The Kolomental crooner, took to his Instagram page to break the sad news to his fans, he posted a collage video of his mother, as he wrote, “I don’t know how to express what’s in my heart. My heart is heavy. My mum passed on last Wednesday, January 12th. This, after my twin sister left this world last year. I don’t know why so many good people I love are leaving but I just hold on to the thought that God is God and he knows what he is doing. It is well. I just thank him that she lived a full life amd is done with the troubles of the world . Rest well mummy!!”  See post below: 